{"id": 231298188, "title": "NEMA Supports Borno To Resettle IDPs", "text": "...Begin Food Distribution for Other IDPs ABUJA \u2013 The Federal Government through the National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) has supported the Borno state Government with food items to resettle IDPs from eight local government areas of the state residing in Muna Garage IDP camp. These include IDPs from Bama, Konduga, Gwoza, Ngala and Jere LGAs that were residing at the Muna Garage IDP camp which is being closed down by the state Government. The Director General NEMA Zubaida Umar who was represented by Director Relief and Rehabilitation Alhaji Abdullahi Adamu Usur was at Muna Garage IDP camp Maiduguri to present the food items to the state Governor Engineer Baba Gana Zulum on behalf of the federal government. The approved items handed over for this intervention include: 35,531 bags of Rice (10 kg); 27,865 bags of beans (10 kg); 24,736 bags of maize (10 kg); 2,501 kegs of vegetable oil (20 litres); 2,025 cartons of tomato paste; 1,614 cartons of seasoning cubes (20 kg); and 837 bags of iodized salt (20 kg). A statement by NEMA on Saturday in Abuja said that presently, NEMA reaches out to 27 locations in the state. The Governor received the items on behalf of the Returning IDPs at Muna IDP camp where the flag off of the routine Distribution of food items for the reurnees and other IDPs residing in other camps was conducted. The statement said that the Governor appreciated the gesture and support of the federal government through NEMA in catering for the welfare of IDPs in Borno State throughout the period of the insurgency. In 2015/16, NEMA signed a Memorandum of Understanding with the Government of Borno State to jointly provide relief assistance to the displaced population in camps.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0072.jpg\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-th